dark matter, leaving just 6% baryonic matter.
94 / 6 &gt; 15 / 1

Now, to get that figure down to ~ what you need for the concordance
model, you will have to postulate:

1) Vastly more baryonic than dark matter outside of galaxies.
2) Vastly more baryonic matter outside of galaxies, than inside.
3) In view of the resultant opacity problem, you now have to
speculate
that most of the mass of the universe is intergalactic  _baryonic_
bricks.

As I have already posted under the other title, &quot;show me my ad hoc
assumptions, and I will show you yours.&quot;

